text: This is a list of State Register of Heritage Places in the Town of Mosman Park, Western Australia. The State Register of Heritage Places is maintained by the Heritage Council of Western Australia. As of 2020, 89 places are heritage-listed in the Town of Mosman Park, of which seven are on the State Register of Heritage Places. ==List== The Western Australian State Register of Heritage Places, as of 2020, lists the following seven state registered places within the Town of Mosman Park: {| class="wikitable sortable" !Place name !Place # !Location !Suburb or town !Co-ordinates !Built !Stateregistered !class="unsortable"|Notes & former names !class="unsortable"|Photo |- |Leighton Battery | |Corner Stirling Highway & Boundary Road |Mosman Park | |1942 |27 August 1999 |Buckland Hill Tunnels and Citizen Military Force Training Battery |140px |- |Memorial Hall | |12 Lochee Street |Mosman Park | |1921 |27 August 1999 |Mosman Park Town Hall, Camelot Picture, Theatre, Road Boards Building, Buckland Hill | |- |St Luke's Anglican Church Group | |16 & 18 Monument Street & 1 Willis Street |Mosman Park | |1897 |27 August 1999 |Consists of Church, Rectory & Alexandra Hall |140px |- |House at 2 Hill Terrace | |2 Hill Terrace |Mosman Park | |1934 |29 September 2015 | | |- |St Luke's Anglican Church | |16 Monument Street |Mosman Park | | | |Part of St Luke's Anglican Church Group Precinct () | |- |The Rectory | |1 Willis Street |Mosman Park | | | |Part of St Luke's Anglican Church Group Precinct () | |- |Alexandra Hall | |16 Monument Street |Mosman Park | | | |Part of St Luke's Anglican Church Group Precinct () | |} ==References== Mosman
